Pounding rains, a week of soft soaking rain, flash floods, army helicopter rescues, homes swept away, two people dead – it was a dramatic week of weather South Africans hadn’t seen for a while … and dams are still in bad shape. Rand Water’s latest figures (as of yesterday) showed there was still room for improvement despite the Lesotho Highlands Water Project reopening on December 4, with the Vaal Dam at 41.03%, Sterkfontein at 91.2%, Grootdraai at 107.2%, and Bloemhof at 68.6%. On Friday, the department of water and sanitation noted national dam levels dropped from 57.6% to 56.1% last...